Final Product Vision

A user should be able to:

Discover a course.
Register.
Watch lectures like CS50.
Read notes and resources.
Complete quizzes.
Write code in the browser.
Submit assignments.
Receive automatic grading.
Interact with mentors.
Join community discussions.
Build portfolio projects.
Earn verified certificates.
Apply for jobs.
Be hired through On2Code.



## and also things to add 


Option 1: Use GitHub First (Fastest MVP)

Students sign in with GitHub.

Student
   │
   ▼
GitHub Account
   │
   ▼
On2Code Course
   │
   ▼
Assignment Repository
   │
   ▼
Auto Grader

Example:

on2code-student-john/
├── week1/
├── week2/
├── week3/
└── project/

Advantages:

Fast to build
No infrastructure cost
Students learn Git professionally
Easy portfolio building

Disadvantages:

GitHub owns the repositories
You're dependent on GitHub APIs
Less control
Option 2: Create On2Code GitHub Organization

This is what I would do first.

On2Code Organization
│
├── student-john-cs101
├── student-mary-cs101
├── student-david-cs101
└── project-repositories

Example:

github.com/on2code

When a student enrolls:

Student Registers
        │
        ▼
On2Code Creates Repository
        │
        ▼
Student Gets Access
        │
        ▼
Push Code
        │
        ▼
Auto Grade

This is very similar to how many coding schools operate.

Option 3: Build Your Own Git Platform (Best Long-Term)

This is what companies like GitHub, GitLab, and SourceHut do.

Architecture:

On2Code
│
├── Authentication
├── Repository Service
├── Git Service
├── Pull Requests
├── Commits
├── Branches
├── Code Review
└── Auto Grading

Student experience:

On2Code Dashboard
      │
      ▼
Repositories
      │
      ▼
My Assignments
      │
      ▼
Push Code
      │
      ▼
Automatic Tests
      │
      ▼
Grade
What I Recommend
Phase 1 (Months 1-6)

Use GitHub.

On2Code
      │
      ▼
GitHub Organization
      │
      ▼
Repositories
      │
      ▼
Auto Grader

This gets you launched quickly.

Phase 2 (Months 6-18)

Deploy your own Git server.

Use:

Gitea

or

Forgejo

These are open-source GitHub alternatives.

Architecture:

On2Code
│
├── LMS
├── Auto Grader
├── Gitea
└── PostgreSQL

Benefits:

Full ownership
Lower cost
Student repositories stay inside On2Code
Easier integration with grading
Phase 3 (Future)

Build an internal service called:

On2Code Repos

similar to GitHub.

Features:

Repositories
Commits
Branches
Pull Requests
Issues
Code Reviews
Actions
CI/CD
Auto Grading
The Submission Flow I Would Build
Student Opens Assignment
         │
         ▼
Repository Created
         │
         ▼
Student Codes
         │
         ▼
Commit
         │
         ▼
